Q.4. Next Greater Power of 2

Description :

Question:
Given a number N, find its next immediate greater power of 2(i.e 2^1, 2^2, 2^3...).


Input Description:
The input consists of a number N where N <= 1000.


Sample Input:
4


Sample Output:
8

=> Code Solution :-
-> Approach 1 :
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
        int N = input.nextInt();
        int multiple = 2;
        for(int i = 1; i <= 1000; i++){
            int Result = N * multiple;
            System.out.println(Result);
            break;
        }
        input.close();
    }
}

-> Approach 2 :
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner input = new Scanner(System.in);
        
        if (input.hasNextInt()) {
            int N = input.nextInt();
            int power = 2; // Start with the first relevant power of 2

            // While the current power is less than or equal to N, 
            // keep moving to the next power
            while (power <= N) {
                power = power * 2;
            }

            System.out.println(power);
        }
        
        input.close();
    }
}

